main event: A witness reported seeing four spherical objects in Rego Park, Queens, New York on July 23, 1955, observing their movements for approximately 30 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were seen moving in pairs, alternately traveling west to east and east to west,The color of the observed objects was described as similar to that of a light bulb,The investigation suggested that the sighting might have been caused by nearby searchlight activity in Times Square,Other potential explanations were ruled out after investigative interviews with local police,The sighting is documented as part of Project Blue Book's investigations into UFO phenomena.
witness description: A 24-year-old automobile insurance adjuster and his wife and landlady, who were all present during the observation.
